cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.LF, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the semantics of a programming language (PCF) and its definability properties, which are topics typically studied in the sub-fields of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of games and strategies in the intensional model suggests a connection to game semantics (cs.TL) and proof theory (cs.LF). Finally, the mention of an effective version and a Universality Theorem suggests a connection to computability theory (cs.CC).
